                    <span>This is just one of the many Mr. Marchaj has written on boat design theory. Yacht must look good and be safe ( read seaworthy). In some instances it must also perform. Performance has no value if it can't handle the challange of the seas. "Seaworthiness, the forgotten factor" disects yacht safety down to most intricate detail. Simply, if you haven't read this book, you don't know it all. An absolute 5 star publication, written with great authority, by one of the most respected in the field. Check out Marchaj's other work as well, he never disappoints.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">An unemotional, realistic view of boats and behaviors.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
